-800x534.jpg 800w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/MarcusWestberg_WildDogs-320x213.jpg 320w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/MarcusWestberg_WildDogs-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/MarcusWestberg_WildDogs-450x300.jpg 450w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/MarcusWestberg_WildDogs-300x200.jpg 300w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/MarcusWestberg_WildDogs-120x80.jpg 120w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/MarcusWestberg_WildDogs.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption id=\"caption-attachment-791538\"\u003eMarcus Westberg (Portugal): African Wild Dog puppies, Tswalu Kalahari Nature Reserve, South Africa\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e \u003cfigure id=\"attachment_791537\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-791537\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Remembering-Wildlife-2025-16-of-18-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"Two tigers lie side by side in the shade beneath dense trees, gazing into the sunlit grassland that stretches beyond the forest. The warm light creates a soft, natural atmosphere.\" width=\"800\" height=\"534\" srcset=\"https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Remembering-Wildlife-2025-16-of-18-800x534.jpg 800w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Remembering-Wildlife-2025-16-of-18-320x213.jpg 320w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Remembering-Wildlife-2025-16-of-18-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Remembering-Wildlife-2025-16-of-18-450x300.jpg 450w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Remembering-Wildlife-2025-16-of-18-300x200.jpg 300w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Remembering-Wildlife-2025-16-of-18-120x80.jpg 120w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Remembering-Wildlife-2025-16-of-18.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption id=\"caption-attachment-791537\"\u003eMark Meth-Cohn (UK): Tigers, Ranthambore Tiger Reserve, India\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e \u003cfigure id=\"attachment_791535\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-791535\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Rwanda-travel-KPF_1827-bewerkt-640x800.jpg\" alt=\"A black and white photo of an adult gorilla gazing tenderly at a smiling baby gorilla, who is lying close and looking up at the adult. The background is dark, highlighting their faces and expressions.\" width=\"640\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Rwanda-travel-KPF_1827-bewerkt-640x800.jpg 640w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Rwanda-travel-KPF_1827-bewerkt-256x320.jpg 256w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Rwanda-travel-KPF_1827-bewerkt-1229x1536.jpg 1229w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Rwanda-travel-KPF_1827-bewerkt.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption id=\"caption-attachment-791535\"\u003eKim Paffen (Netherlands): Mountain Gorilla and her baby, Volcanoes National Park, Rwanda\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e \u003cfigure id=\"attachment_791534\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-791534\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Sloth-Bear-1-of-1-800x545.jpg\" alt=\"A sloth bear stands in the doorway of a weathered, red-walled building with a green door, surrounded by overgrown grass and plants.\" width=\"800\" height=\"545\" srcset=\"https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Sloth-Bear-1-of-1-800x545.jpg 800w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Sloth-Bear-1-of-1-320x218.jpg 320w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Sloth-Bear-1-of-1-1536x1046.jpg 1536w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Sloth-Bear-1-of-1.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption id=\"caption-attachment-791534\"\u003eMark Meth-Cohn (UK): Sloth bear, Ranthambore Tiger Reserve, India\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e \u003cfigure id=\"attachment_791533\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-791533\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Sunset-Scales-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"A close-up of a pangolin, showing its overlapping brown scales in warm sunlight as it bends down to the ground, highlighting the texture and pattern of its armored body.\" width=\"800\" height=\"534\" srcset=\"https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Sunset-Scales-800x534.jpg 800w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Sunset-Scales-320x213.jpg 320w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Sunset-Scales-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Sunset-Scales-450x300.jpg 450w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Sunset-Scales-300x200.jpg 300w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Sunset-Scales-120x80.jpg 120w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Sunset-Scales.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption id=\"caption-attachment-791533\"\u003eArmand Grobler (South Africa): Pangolin, Manyeleti Game Reserve, Greater Kruger, South Africa\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e \u003cfigure id=\"attachment_791532\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-791532\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Xavier-Ortega-3-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"Four cheetahs lie closely together on grass, looking in different directions while rain falls around them. The image is in black and white, creating a dramatic and serene mood.\" width=\"800\" height=\"534\" srcset=\"https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Xavier-Ortega-3-800x534.jpg 800w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Xavier-Ortega-3-320x213.jpg 320w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Xavier-Ortega-3-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Xavier-Ortega-3-450x300.jpg 450w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Xavier-Ortega-3-300x200.jpg 300w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Xavier-Ortega-3-120x80.jpg 120w, https://petapixel.com/assets/uploads/2025/04/Xavier-Ortega-3.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption id=\"caption-attachment-791532\"\u003eXavier Ortega (Spain): Cheetahs, Masai Mara, Kenya\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n \u003cp\u003eThis year’s contest jury included leading wildlife photographers Art Wolfe and Federico Veronesi, each longtime contributors to the broader \u003cem\u003eRemembering Wildlife\u003c/em\u003e series themselves. \u003c/p\u003e \u003cp\u003e“Although it made our judging very challenging, we were delighted by the incredibly high standard of images submitted. If only we’d had space, so many more could easily have graced the pages of this year’s book,” says head judge and \u003cem\u003eRemembering Wildlife\u003c/em\u003e founder and producer, Margot Raggett MBE. \u003c/p\u003e \u003cp\u003eA Kickstarter campaign to raise the necessary funds to produce the book — at least $26,540 — has been live since March and smashed its goal, raising nearly $200,000. There are still a few days left for customers to get in on the ground floor and purchase the \u003cem\u003e10 Years of Remembering Wildlife\u003c/em\u003e photography book for as little as £50, or about $67. Complete backing details are \u003ca href=\"https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/margotraggett/10-years-of-remembering-wildlife\" data-wpel-link=\"external\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"follow external noopener\"\u003eavailable on Kickstarter\u003c/a\u003e. \u003c/p\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe book will also be available separately via \u003ca href=\"https://rememberingwildlife.com/\" data-wpel-link=\"external\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"follow external noopener\"\u003ethe Remembering Wildlife website\u003c/a\u003e. The book is expected to launch on October 6, 2025. \u003c/p\u003e \u003chr/\u003e \u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eImage credits:\u003c/strong\u003e Remembering Wildlife. Individual photographers are credited in the image captions. \u003c/em\u003e \u003c/p\u003e \u003chr/\u003e \u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDisclaimer\u003c/strong\u003e: Make sure you do your own research into any crowdfunding project you’re considering backing. While we aim to only share legitimate and trustworthy campaigns, there’s always a real chance that you can lose your money when backing any crowdfunded project. PetaPixel does not participate in any crowdfunding affiliate programs.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eTo hold projects accountable, all crowdfunding campaigns on which PetaPixel reports are financially backed with the lowest tier option in order to give the publication visibility into all backer-only communications. If a campaign owner acts in a manner inconsistent with its promises, PetaPixel will share that information publicly.\u003cbr/\u003e \u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n      \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
